{{Lua|Module:EPBC status}}

== Usage ==

To show a species' conservation status under Australia's [[Environment Protection and Biodiversity Conservation Act 1999]] (EPBC Act), as an inline coloured badge with an optional reference link to the [[Species Profile and Threats Database]] (SPRAT).

* {{tlx|EPBC status|{{var|status}}|{{var|sprat_taxon_id}}|{{var|option}}}}

This is the EPBC analogue of {{tl|IUCN status}}. The EPBC Act ({{EPBC Act 1999 section|178|s178}}) lists threatened species in exactly six categories, which deliberately mirror the [[IUCN Red List]] categories; this template reuses the {{tl|IUCN status}} colour palette for visual consistency.

== Parameters ==
* {{var|status}} is the only required parameter — one of the six EPBC categories: '''EX''', '''EW''', '''CR''', '''EN''', '''VU''', '''CD''' (case-insensitive). '''DL''' (Delisted) is also accepted as a display state.
* {{var|sprat_taxon_id}} is the species' SPRAT Taxon ID, found in the profile URL <nowiki>https://www.environment.gov.au/cgi-bin/sprat/public/publicspecies.pl?taxon_id=</nowiki>'''86568'''
* If {{var|option}} is set to
:'''1''' or '''12''' (and a SPRAT Taxon ID is given), an external reference link to the SPRAT species profile is appended.
:'''2''' or '''12''', an internal link to the article about the given category is provided.
* {{para|year}} sets the year shown in the external link label (e.g. "EPBC 2024"); {{para|label}} overrides the link text entirely.

